<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Chocolate Cake | Taste The Movies</title>
</head>
<body>

  <header>
    <h1>Taste The Movies</h1>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section>
      <div>
        <img src="images/placeholder.png" alt="Chocolate Cake from the movie Matilda" />
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2>Decadent Fudge Chocolate Cake</h2>
        <p><strong>Description:</strong></p>
        <p>Yes, it’s that one. Bruce's masterpiece, a rich and fudgy chocolate cake made famous in the movie <em>Matilda</em>.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div>
        <h3>Ingredients</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>1¾ cups flour</li>
          <li>2 cups sugar</li>
          <li>¾ cup cocoa powder</li>
          <li>1½ tsp baking powder</li>
          <li>1½ tsp baking soda</li>
          <li>2 eggs</li>
          <li>1 cup milk</li>
          <li>½ cup vegetable oil</li>
          <li>2 tsp vanilla extract</li>
          <li>1 cup hot coffee</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>Instructions</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C) and grease two round cake pans.</li>
          <li>Mix all dry ingredients (flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking powder, and baking soda) in a bowl.</li>
          <li>Add eggs, milk, oil, and vanilla extract. Stir until smooth.</li>
          <li>Slowly stir in hot coffee last. The batter will be thin.</li>
          <li>Pour the batter into the prepared pans and bake for 30–35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.</li>
          <li>Let the cakes cool before frosting with chocolate ganache or buttercream.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
  </footer>

</body>
</html>

